d=3D[UNIQID]) =2C a state of essential evolutionary and existential signi=
ficance. Egan speaks to it beautifully:

When I=E2=80=99m writing fiction I forget who I am and what I come from. I=
 slip into utter absorption mode. I love the sense that I=E2=80=99ve becom=
e so engaged with the other side=2C I=E2=80=99ve slightly lost my bearings=
 here. If I=E2=80=99m going from the writing mind-set to picking my kids u=
p from school=2C I often feel a very short but acute kind of depression=2C=
 as if I have the bends. Once I=E2=80=99m with them it totally disappears=
=2C and I feel happy again. Sometimes I forget I have children=2C which is=
 very strange. I feel guilty about it=2C as if my inattention will cause s=
omething to happen to them=2C even when I=E2=80=99m not responsible for th=
em=E2=80=A6

Illustration by Kris Di Giacomo from Enormous Smallness (https://www.brain=
pickings.org/2015/03/30/enormous-smallness-e-e-cummings-matthew-burgess/?m=
c_cid=3D1ffb15db80&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) by Matthew Burgess=2C a picture-boo=
