In a sentiment that calls to mind Joni Mitchell=E2=80=99s reflections on t=
he dark side of artistic success (https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/09/22=
/joni-mitchell-in-her-own-words-malka-marom/?mc_cid=3D1ffb15db80&mc_eid=3D=
[UNIQID]) and John Steinbeck=E2=80=99s lamentation about the perils of pu=
blic approval (https://www.brainpickings.org/2015/05/13/john-steinbeck-wor=
king-days-fame-success/?mc_cid=3D1ffb15db80&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =2C Egan c=
onsiders the psychoemotional aftermath of her Pulitzer win:

The attention and approval I=E2=80=99ve been getting for Goon Squad (http:=
//www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0307477479/braipick-20?mc_cid=3D1ffb15db=
80&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =E2=80=94 the very public moments of winning the Pu=
litzer and the other prizes =E2=80=94 is exactly the opposite of the very=
 private pleasure of writing. And it=E2=80=99s dangerous. Thinking that I=
=E2=80=99ll get this kind of love again=2C that getting it should be my go=
al=2C would lead me to creative decisions that would undermine me and my w=
ork. I=E2=80=99ve never sought that approval=2C which is all the more reas=
on that I don=E2=80=99t want to start now.

[=E2=80=A6]

My whole creative endeavor is the repudiation of my last work with the new=
 one. If I start craving approval=2C trying to replicate what I did with G=
oon Squad=2C it=E2=80=99s never going to lead to anything good. I know tha=
t. Stop getting better? There=E2=80=99s no excuse for that.

With an eye to our propensity for what psychologists call the =E2=80=9Cend=
 of history illusion=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 best captured by Harvard psycholog=
ist Dan Gilbert=E2=80=99s aphoristic summation that =E2=80=9Chuman beings=
 are works in progress [who] mistakenly think they=E2=80=99re finished=E2=
=80=9D (https://www.brainpickings.org/2014/06/18/daniel-gilbert-happiness-=
future-self/?mc_cid=3D1ffb15db80&mc_eid=3D[UNIQID]) =E2=80=94 Egan adds:

We all have such a tendency to think the present moment will last forever.=
 Maybe when I=E2=80=99m not the flavor of the month anymore I=E2=80=99ll b=
e devastated and shocked=2C and I=E2=80=99ll forget everything I=E2=80=99m=
